Being that it is the first answer that addresses the issues of denial of care bullshit, as well as denial of coverage, yes. While I think it will take a few years to get the kinks out once it gets rolling, we will see vast improvements in our total level of health as a nation. Of course, equally important is that we start living healthier lifestyles, but, one thing at a time, I guess?